Former Bloemfontein Celtic Football Club midfielder, Kabelo Mahlasela joined Polokwane City Football Club last Thursday.
The industrious midfielder was on the books of Kaizer Chiefs Football Club and joins City on a five-month loan until the end of the season.
He made a debut for Rise and Shine during their 0-1 defeat at the hands of their nemesis, Baroka Football Club at the new Peter Mokaba Stadium on Saturday.
He is expected to be in the team starting line-up when they host Golden Arrows at Peter Mokaba Stadium on Sunday.
